<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Trawma Siirjen on 04-04-2001 01:03 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">The answer is simple.  Whoever spawns and kills Ragefire deserves the kill and the associated reward.  It's irrelevant who camped what for who knows how long.  Does the PnP say that someone sitting down near a spawn means that the person owns that spawn?  If so, can I sit next to a large wasp drone, claiming ownership, just to protect it from the rabid noobies.  "Don't kill this wasp, I'm medding up. It's MY spawn, though!"  How long do I deserve the claim?  Can I sit for 2 hours protecting the wasp?  This is the stupidity that I see here.

I do play by the PnP, but I don't agree with any of it.  Having been on Vallon Zek for 20 months, both as a PKr and a good guy, I am disgusted by the way disputes are handled in the carebear environment.  It is horrible roleplay, and not very fun at all, to not be able to claim ownership simply by mobilizing a force and wiping out whoever is camping.

Do you roleplayers feel comfortable seeing a Paladin and a Troll discussing who gets to kill the next spawn?  I just can't understand how this mentality makes any sense wihtin Norrath, or how it is fun, and I'm not even a big roleplayer.

I don't believe that might makes right, but I do believe that a mighty force is justified in taking whatever they damn well please.  In the case of Ragefire ownership on carebear servers.  I guess the GMs have to sort out who "owns" the camp, since they made the silly rules to begin with.  Tis a shame that GM's decide these things when clearly the game engine should have been built to allow for combat to settle this crap.

Given the complete lack of insight, and associated code, by Verant on these issues, I think whoever kill steals it first is completely justified in that action.  In the same respect, I believe that a monk who causes a train and FD's right in front of the kill stealer is ALSO justified in doing so.  The PnP is ridiculous to enforce.  Great as a code of ethics.  But a horrible way to determine who gets to kill a MoB.  Laughable at best.

My opinions are extreme even for the Zek servers.  However, we are a resilient bunch on VZ.  You respawn, you loot yer corpse, you go back to what you were doing.  You learn to be strong as a noobie.

An armed society is a polite society.

Trawma Siirjen
45 High Elf Cleric
United Legions
Vallon Zek
(and many others - some nice, some nasty as hell)</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
